From b1e03bc0344160312247b69f7943465dd5fc4cd8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Inochi Amaoto <inochiama@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 16 Mar 2026 09:00:38 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 020/586] UPSTREAM: net: stmmac: platform: Add snps,dwmac-5.40a
 IP compatible string

Add compatible string for 5.40a version that can avoid to define some
platform data in the glue layer.

Signed-off-by: Inochi Amaoto <inochiama@gmail.com>
Reviewed-by: Russell King (Oracle) <rmk+kernel@armlinux.org.uk>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20260316010041.164360-3-inochiama@gmail.com
Signed-off-by: Jakub Kicinski <kuba@kernel.org>
(cherry picked from commit d35aa97ea908a17809358a981bef6cd752f2e8a0)
Signed-off-by: Han Gao <gaohan@iscas.ac.cn>
Signed-off-by: Mingcong Bai <jeffbai@aosc.io>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/stmmac_platform.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/stmmac_platform.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/stmmac_platform.c
index 5c9fd91a1db9d..02303a808fb56 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/stmmac_platform.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/stmmac_platform.c
@@ -396,6 +396,7 @@ static const char * const stmmac_gmac4_compats[] = {
 	"snps,dwmac-5.10a",
 	"snps,dwmac-5.20",
 	"snps,dwmac-5.30a",
+	"snps,dwmac-5.40a",
 	NULL
 };
 
